 Do's**

1. Keep your profiles on a privacy setting and regularly review who can see your posts.
2. Think before you post — ask yourself if you'd be comfortable with a professor or future employer seeing it.
3. Give proper credit when sharing someone else's work, photos, or ideas.
4. Use social media to build a positive personal brand — share achievements, projects, and learning.
5. Verify information before sharing — check the source and cross-reference with credible outlets.
6. Set screen time limits and take regular digital detoxes to protect your mental health.
7. Use strong, unique passwords and enable 2FA on all your social media accounts.
8. Report and block accounts that send suspicious links, inappropriate messages, or harass you.

---

Don'ts**

1. Don't share your location, address, phone number, or daily routine publicly.
2. Don't post or share content in anger or frustration — always pause and reflect first.
3. Don't plagiarise or repost others' content without attribution or permission.
4. Don't engage in or encourage cyberbullying, trolling, or online harassment of any kind.
5. Don't spread unverified news, rumours, or misinformation, even if it seems believable.
6. Don't compare your life, grades, or appearance to others' curated online personas.
7. Don't use the same password across multiple platforms or share login credentials with anyone.
8. Don't click on unfamiliar links or respond to messages from unknown accounts.
